name: HENthousand Tezcatlipoca
description: An offering for #HENthousand - a recoloured image of the Aztec deity Tezcatlipoca from the Codex Borgia. This deity goes by many names which allude to his different aspects: Titlacauan ("We Are His Slaves"), Ipalnemoani ("He by Whom We Live"), Necoc Yaotl ("Enemy of Both Sides"), and Tloque Nahuaque ("Lord of the Near and the Nigh")
